place.name: TURKDEAN
place.gazetteerText: TURKDEAN, a parish in Northleach district, Gloucester; 4½ miles SW of Bourton-on-the-Water r. station Post town, Northleach, under Cheltenham. Acres, 1,890. Real property, £2,064. Pop., 291. Houses, 62. The property is divided among four. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Gloucester and Bristol. Value, £208.* Patron, Christchurch, Oxford. The church is Norman. There are a national school and charities £36. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
